9#ifndef ltable_h
10#define ltable_h
11
12#include "lobject.h"
13
14
15#define gnode(t,i) (&(t)->node[i])
16#define gval(n) (&(n)->i_val)
17#define gnext(n) ((n)->i_key.nk.next)
18
19
20/* 'const' to avoid wrong writings that can mess up field 'next' */
21#define gkey(n) cast(const TValue*, (&(n)->i_key.tvk))
22
23/*
24** writable version of 'gkey'; allows updates to individual fields,
25** but not to the whole (which has incompatible type)
26*/
27#define wgkey(n) (&(n)->i_key.nk)
28
29#define invalidateTMcache(t) ((t)->flags = 0)
30
31
32/* true when 't' is using 'dummynode' as its hash part */
33#define isdummy(t) ((t)->lastfree == NULL)
34
35
36/* allocated size for hash nodes */
37#define allocsizenode(t) (isdummy(t) ? 0 : sizenode(t))
38
39
40/* returns the key, given the value of a table entry */
41#define keyfromval(v) \
42 (gkey(cast(Node *, cast(char *, (v)) - offsetof(Node, i_val))))
43
